programme.title: Xena: Warrior Princess

Xena: Lucy Lawless. Gabrielle: Renee O'Connor.

programme.title: Xena: Warrior Princess

programme.title: Xena: Warrior Princess

Chris Evans, Michael Chiklis, Julian McMahon. Directed by Tim Story.

programme.title: The Purge: Anarchy

programme.title: Battleship

programme.desc: Caroline takes Max with her to visit her father in prison.

programme.title: 2 Broke Girls
programme.desc: Max and Caroline enjoy a spring getaway when they take care of a dog at a couple's ritzy apartment.

programme.title: 2 Broke Girls
programme.desc: Max and Caroline participate in a clinical drug trial to raise money to help Caroline's father.

programme.title: Friends
programme.desc: Conclusion. Monica and Rachel meet two cute doctors; Ross looks to Jack for fatherly advice; Phoebe confronts her twin about Joey. Jack: Elliot Gould. Admissions Woman: Alaina Reed Hall. Monica: Courteney Cox.

programme.sub-title: The One with the Breast Milk
programme.desc: Monica goes shopping with Julie (Lauren Tom)---behind Rachel's back; Ross isn't exactly gaga over breast milk. Carol: Jane Sibbett. Susan: Jessica Hecht. Hombre Guy: Joel Beeson.

programme.title: Friends
programme.sub-title: The One After the Super Bowl
programme.desc: Conclusion. Ross learns Marcel is working on a movie, and the film's makeup artist seems to want Chandler; Monica and Rachel fight over Jean-Claude Van Damme, who appears as himself. Susie: Julia Roberts.

programme.title: Friends
programme.sub-title: The One with the Prom Video
programme.desc: Monica brings some things home from her parents' house, including a prom video; Rachel tells Ross that she doesn't think it will work out between them.

programme.title: Friends
programme.desc: Phoebe undergoes in-vitro fertilization; Monica and Rachel go up against Joey and Chandler to determine which pair know the other better. Frank Jr.: Giovanni Ribisi. Alice: Debra Jo Rupp. Phoebe: Lisa Kudrow.

programme.title: Friends
programme.sub-title: The One with All the Wedding Dresses
programme.desc: Monica tries on Emily's wedding dress; Ross's plans affect Rachel and Joshua; Chandler insists Joey get help for his snoring. Joshua: Tate Donovan. Saleswoman: Anne Betancourt. Marjorie: Christine Moore.

programme.title: Friends
programme.sub-title: The One with the Thanksgiving Flashbacks
programme.desc: The gang reflects on bad Thanksgivings---and the biggest turkey belongs to Monica, who recalls her first encounter with Chandler (Matthew Perry). Nora: Morgan Fairchild. Young Chandler: Joshua Preston.

programme.title: Friends
programme.sub-title: The One with Joey's Big Break
programme.desc: Joey is cast in an independent film to be shot in the desert outside Las Vegas; Phoebe's angry with Ross. Dr. Miller: Michael Monks. Chandler: Matthew Perry. Rachel: Jennifer Aniston. Phoebe: Lisa Kudrow.

programme.title: Friends
programme.sub-title: The One on the Last Night
programme.desc: Parting is such sweet---and amusing---sorrow as Rachel and Chandler prepare to vacate their respective apartments, and their soon-to-be ex-roommates make certain their last night will be a memorable one. Chandler: Matthew Perry. Joey: Matt LeBlanc.

programme.title: Friends
programme.sub-title: The One Where Rachel Has a Baby
programme.desc: Conclusion. The birth of Ross and Rachel's baby leads to a surprising turn of events for the proud parents. Cliff: Eddie McClintock. Dr. Long: Amanda Carlin. Janice: Maggie Wheeler.

programme.title: Friends
programme.sub-title: The One with Rachel's Going-Away Party
programme.desc: The gang plans a going-away party for Rachel, but rather than face them together she offers each a private goodbye, but one of the guys takes it the wrong way when he's excluded. Also: Monica prepares for life in the suburbs; and she and Chandler keep a watchful eye on the mother (Anna Faris) of their future adopted child.

programme.title: Young Sheldon
programme.sub-title: Summer Sausage, a Pocket Poncho, and Tony Danza
programme.desc: While Sheldon is busy keeping tabs on Meemaw's budding relationship with Dr. Sturgis, George Sr. and Mary attempt to bond with their other children.

programme.title: Young Sheldon
programme.sub-title: Vanilla Ice Cream, Gentleman Callers, and a Dinette Set
programme.desc: When Meemaw is pursued by two gentlemen callers, Sheldon interferes, forcing her to set some ground rule. The Season 1 finale.

programme.title: The Woman in White
programme.desc: In 1851 England, a young artist goes to a grand estate to give painting lessons to a beautiful young woman, only to discover an eccentric cast of characters filling out the house.

programme.title: Rhapsody in Blue
programme.desc: Fictionalized account of the life and musical times of composer George Gershwin traces his rise from a "song plugger" for a Manhattan music-publishing company to the heights of international fame and fortune. Features more than 20 Gershwin compositions and Al Jolson jolting out "Swanee."

programme.title: The Case of the Black Cat
programme.desc: One of the best of the Perry Mason series, with Ricardo Cortez as the lawyer-detective trying to solve three murders, all of which have been heralded by the screech of a feline.

programme.title: The Green Slime
programme.desc: Astronauts on a space station are plagued by a mysterious jellylike substance that clings to their backs, then turns into tentacled, red-eyed creatures that kill their victims.

programme.title: White Mane
programme.desc: Albert Lamorisse's lyrical short film about a young boy who becomes attached to a wild horse in the Camargue region of France. Alain Emery, Pascal Lamorisse.

programme.title: The Yellow Rolls-Royce
programme.desc: The ups and downs of a number of varied and amorous owners of the same elegant car and how it affects their lives from the 1920s to World War II.

programme.title: Breakin'
programme.desc: A rebellious dance student falls in with a group of breakdancers and begins performing with them.

programme.title: Smithereens
programme.desc: The study of a teenager struggling to succeed as a new-wave singer in New York City.

programme.title: Foxes
programme.desc: Four teen girls in California wrestle with sex, drugs, and bad parents, using each other for emotional support.

programme.title: Pink Floyd: The Wall
programme.desc: Alan Parker's surreal visualization of the classic LP traces the life of an alienated rock star who builds a metaphorical wall to separate himself from his emotional pain.

programme.title: Fame
programme.desc: A chronicle of the lives of several teenagers who attend a New York high school for students gifted in the performing arts.

programme.title: Absolute Beginners
programme.desc: Director Julien Temple's energetic, stylized musical about 1958 British teens at the dawn of rock and roll, featuring David Bowie, the Kinks' Ray Davies and Sade. Eddie O'Connell, Patsy Kensit. Henley: James Fox. Big Jill: Eve Ferret. Fanatic: Steven Berkoff. Dido: Anita Morris.

programme.title: Once You Kiss a Stranger
programme.desc: Murder by surrogate binds a golf pro to a psychotic lady.

programme.title: Hands of a Stranger
programme.desc: A pianist (James Stapleton), injured in an accident, has the hands of a murderer grafted onto him. Talky, but the arty camera work is effective. Dina: Joan Harvey. Holly: Irish McCalla. Skeet: Barry Gordon. Harding: Paul Lukather. Directed by Newt Arnold.

programme.title: The Tattooed Stranger
programme.desc: Neat whodunit as New York's finest go after a killer. John Miles, Patricia White (Barry), Walter Kinsella, Frank Twedell. Made in New York, which adds to the authenticity. Edward J. Montagne directed.

programme.title: Stranger on the Third Floor
programme.desc: An aspiring journalist testifies he saw a young man at the scene of a brutal killing and the man is sentenced to death. The journalist worries he is responsible for the death of an innocent man and begins his own investigation with his wife, but the duo soon find themselves threatened by a mysterious stranger.

programme.title: Walk Softly, Stranger
programme.desc: A gambler (Joseph Cotten) woos a disabled rich girl (Valli) for her money, and finds he's really falling for her. Spring Byington. Whitey: Paul Stewart. Robert Stevenson directed.

programme.title: Talk About a Stranger
programme.desc: A boy becomes obsessed with the idea that his unfriendly neighbor murdered the kid's beloved dog. The child sets off to find evidence, and discovers the man has an unusual past. Eventually the boy engages in an action that has dire consequences for himself and his community.

programme.title: I See a Dark Stranger
programme.desc: A young Irish woman, taught to hate the British, is used by Nazi agents.

programme.title: Strangers on a Train
programme.desc: Alfred Hitchcock's masterful suspense tale of a tennis pro railroaded into a murder pact by a demented playboy, who offers to kill the athlete's unfaithful wife in exchange for him doing away with the rich man's hated father. Raymond Chandler cowrote the script based on Patricia Highsmith's novel. Hitchcock's daughter, Patricia Hitchcock, costars as Barbara Morton, sister of the tennis player's girlfriend.

programme.title: In Harm's Way
programme.desc: A look into the lives of Navy men and their women caught up in the chaos of Japan's attack on Pearl Harbor. John Wayne, Patricia Neal, Kirk Douglas. Jere: Brandon de Wilde. Bev: Paula Prentiss. McConnel: Tom Tryon. Broderick: Dana Andrews. CINCPAC I Admiral: Franchot Tone. Owynn: Patrick O'Neal. Burke: Carroll O'Connor. Powell: Burgess Meredith. CINCPAC II Admiral: Henry Fonda. Gregory: George Kennedy. Based on the novel by James Basset. Directed by Otto Preminger.

programme.title: Battle of the Bulge
programme.desc: Epic, episodic account of the Nazis' last desperate bid to turn the tide of World War II on the Western Front features plenty of action (especially the tank battles).

programme.title: The Crowded Sky
programme.desc: Another group of disaster-bound strangers on board a plane. Dana Andrews, Rhonda Fleming, Efrem Zimbalist Jr. Mike: John Kerr. Kitty: Anne Francis. Nick: Keenan Wynn. McVey: Troy Donahue. Capelli: Joe Mantell. Gertrude: Patsy Kelly. Gloria: Jean Willes. Bev: Nan Leslie. Directed by Joseph Pevney.

programme.title: Brainstorm
programme.desc: Jeffrey Hunter as an unbalanced scientist who falls for the boss's wife (Anne Francis), and feigns insanity in a plot to murder her sadistic husband (Dana Andrews). Dr. Larstadt: Viveca Lindfors. Reynolds: Josh Harris. Directed by actor William Conrad ("Cannon").

programme.title: The Loved One
programme.desc: In Southern California, an innocent British poet falls for a funeral-home cosmetician being wooed by a prissy funeral director who lives with his obese mother in this satire on American funeral rites based on Evelyn Waugh's darkly comic novel.

programme.title: The Satan Bug
programme.desc: A frantic search is undertaken for stolen flasks containing a deadly serum that if unleashed could wipe out all life on Earth.

programme.title: The Frozen Dead

programme.title: The Devil's Brigade
programme.desc: GI misfits team with Canadian commandos for raids in Nazi-occupied Norway. Based on true events.

programme.title: The Kissing Bandit

programme.title: Higher and Higher
